reviews.headline: Impossible to remove; eye irritant
reviews.comments: At first, I loved this mascara because it stayed in place for 24 hours.  No clumping and lashed looked brilliant/full.  Then I tried to remove it.  Over 2 weeks time, I lost eyelashes and my eyes became irritated.  Not worth the look.

reviews.headline: Best Mascara Ever!
reviews.comments: I believe at my young age of 61, I've tried just about every mascara out there over the years.  Not only is the burgundy a most beautiful color that brings out the blue in my eyes, you'd never know it was burgundy. (I had some concerns before using.)  There is ZERO clumping and it truly does lengthen beyond my wildest dreams.  It does not smudge or rub off yet washes off beautifully at the end of the day. Always swore I'd never use "colored" mascara until this beauty.  Highly recommend!!!

reviews.headline: This works but ripped out almost all my eyelashes

Makeup wipes, that Garnier thing water cleanser and my shower of course. It came off eventually but it took almost all the eyelashes with it. I have school in 3 days and now I might not be able to wear mascara until it comes off. The non waterproof version doesn't stay long enough so honestly both are trash. This ruined my life if I'm being so fr.

reviews.headline: Burgundy shade was a bummer
reviews.comments: This mascara has rave reviews, but I was just not at all impressed. The wand feels flimsy, the color payoff is minimal. I purchased the burgundy shade - I have pretty decent natural lashes, and they're blonde, so colored mascaras usually show up really well for me. This one did not; I also didnt feel like it gave me any volume, curl, or lengthening. Maybelline usually nails it for budget mascara, but this one was a bust. I found that more than 2 coats it got got clumpy, and still wasnt pigmented enough.

reviews.headline: this is now my go to daily default
reviews.comments:
I was looking to try out a burgundy mascara and came across this one. Not having super high hopes, I gave it a shot to prove the concept. now she is my daily go to ðŸ¥°

The burgundy color is not super noticeable to me but I believe it does make a difference (I have hazel eyes and I wanted to enhance the green) and a couple of artsy friends commented when asked that they could tell it was burgundy on my already black lashes.

Where this mascara really shines is 1. the wand and 2. the formula. Love love love.

I definitely have to scrape excess product off the tip of the wand, but after that application is super easy and consistent, the brush is flexible but easy to control if you don't press too hard. the longer bristles help pick up every little lash and the narrow tip gets in the corners. 

a minor con is that it's hard to drag through lashes for a second coat once the first coat has dried, so don't let it dry fully before going in for coat #2. you may risk clumping otherwise.

once it dries this formula is super comfortable and does not budge. I have oily skin and it challenges most products I put near my eyes but this stands up.

another minor con is that it takes some effort to remove, but a little micellar water or warm water soak does the trick. it feels like a tubing mascara because it comes off in clumps and strips instead of just dissolving away.

I had a rough week and this didn't smear or flake even after crying. 11/10 already adding this back to my cart so I can repurchase.

reviews.headline: Would but again.
reviews.comments: Ive been a Benefits " theyre real" mascara  wearer forna billion years (10 plus), but my recent tubes are smudging bad, so i had to try skmetjing else out.  Reddit recommended this mascara, and so far I'm happy with it.

reviews.headline: True Brown needs to be more Brown
reviews.comments: Great mascara formula, but please can any brand just do an actual brown? The true brown is pretty much black.

reviews.headline: Read this review trust me!!!
reviews.comments: I personally love the sky high mascara although I'm not very good at actually doing makeup this makes it so simple and easy! I highly recommend this product it's super great my only flaw would be in doesn't hold the curl too well and kinda makes your lashes fall.

reviews.headline: Meh.
reviews.comments: I was excited to try this mascara since it is a best seller and has great reviews. I am disappointed because this mascara basically coats the lashes and makes them clump together like when they are wet, and the more I try to work with it the messier it looks. I am thinking this is just another over-hyped internet thing. Maybelline has other better mascaras than this one.

reviews.headline: Great mascara!
reviews.comments: Does not flake off or give me raccoon eyes even in hot weather. Goes on easily and gives me good length. It's a little hard to remove, even with balm or oil, but small price to pay for stay-put mascara. Will repurchase.

faceoff_positive.comments: I had to try this because so many other influencers have been hyping it up. I figured it would fall flat just because most of the time the hype is not real, haha. Anywaysâ€” I like it! I'll purchase again with my own money because I love how it spreads each lash and gives it a natural, yet emphasized look. My natural lashes aren't super long, but they're not super short either so I always look for length, volume and longevity. In the photo I took, I only used one coat, and it gave me lift, my lashes don't look like spider legs or clumpy (yay). Another thing I really enjoy is after hours of wear IT DIDN'T FLAKE OR RUN down into the corners of my eye or bottom lash line (ya know how you blink and you're like how did that mascara get there?! Yeah that didn't happen with this mascara! This performs well and I highly recommend it. The packaging is so nice too, very luxe feeling. W
faceoff_positive.headline: Mascara delivers length, volume and separation

faceoff_negative.comments: I'm not normally a review writer. This was briefly my favorite mascara. I really loved how my lashes looked with it on and I was able to look past the formula drying out fast. BUT THEN I bought it and the wand was bent and completely unusable! I thought it was maybe a batch issue and returned it and bought a new one, SAME THING! I avoided buying it for a bit and then I bought it at a different store and at this point I'm just fed up with this problem! I'm not buying it again until it's officially fixed everywhere because 3 mascaras with the same defect is just ridiculous.
faceoff_negative.headline: WAND BENT
